### Stream D — The Matchmaker

#### [NEW] [ticket.go](file:///c:/Users/JOHNSON/Desktop/TryBlynx/internal/matchmaker/ticket.go)

```go
type MatchTicket struct {
    UserID       uuid.UUID
    Gender       string   // User's own gender
    TargetGender string   // Desired match gender ("any" if non-VIP)
    Location     string
    Language     string
    Interests    []string
    IsVIP        bool
    Shadowbanned bool
    SubmittedAt  time.Time
}
```

- `SubmitTicket(ticket)` — `ZADD waiting_pool <unix_ts> <userID>` + `HSET ticket:{userID} ...`
- `RemoveTicket(userID)` — `ZREM waiting_pool <userID>` + `DEL ticket:{userID}`

#### [NEW] [worker.go](file:///c:/Users/JOHNSON/Desktop/TryBlynx/internal/matchmaker/worker.go)
**Batch Worker Algorithm (runs as a persistent goroutine):**

```
every 500ms:
    1. ZRANGEBYSCORE waiting_pool -inf +inf  →  all ticket userIDs
    2. Fetch all tickets from Redis HGETALL
    3. Separate into two pools:
         normalPool  = tickets where shadowbanned == false
         shadowPool  = tickets where shadowbanned == true
    4. For each pool independently:
         Sort by SubmittedAt (oldest first = highest priority)
         For each unmatched ticket A:
             waitDuration = now - A.SubmittedAt
             For each remaining unmatched ticket B:
                 if isCompatible(A, B, waitDuration):
                     MATCH(A, B)
                     Remove both from waiting_pool
                     Notify both clients via Hub
                     break
```

**Filter Relaxation (Time-Based):**

```go
func isCompatible(a, b *MatchTicket, waitA, waitB time.Duration) bool {
    maxWait := max(waitA, waitB)

    // 1. STRICT: Gender filter (VIP-only feature)
    if a.IsVIP && a.TargetGender != "any" && b.Gender != a.TargetGender {
        return false
    }
    if b.IsVIP && b.TargetGender != "any" && a.Gender != b.TargetGender {
        return false
    }

    // 2. RELAXABLE: Interests (drop after 10s)
    if maxWait < 10*time.Second {
        if !hasOverlap(a.Interests, b.Interests) {
            return false
        }
    }

    // 3. RELAXABLE: Location (drop after 20s)
    if maxWait < 20*time.Second {
        if a.Location != b.Location {
            return false
        }
    }

    // 4. RELAXABLE: Language (drop after 30s)
    if maxWait < 30*time.Second {
        if a.Language != b.Language {
            return false
        }
    }

    return true
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> The relaxation thresholds (10s, 20s, 30s) are configurable via environment variables. The order of relaxation (Interests → Location → Language) is per the spec.

#### [NEW] [shadowban.go](file:///c:/Users/JOHNSON/Desktop/TryBlynx/internal/matchmaker/shadowban.go)
- The worker separates the ticket pool into `normalPool` and `shadowPool` **before** matching.
- Shadowbanned users are never matched with normal users.
- This is transparent — shadowbanned users see the same UI and get matches (just only with each other).

