## Data Flow Diagrams

### Authentication & WebSocket Connection
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant API as Go HTTP API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant WS as WebSocket Hub

    Client->>API: POST /api/login {email, password}
    API->>DB: SELECT user WHERE email = ?
    API->>API: bcrypt.Compare(password, hash)
    API-->>Client: 200 {token: "eyJ..."}

    Client->>WS: GET /ws?token=eyJ...
    WS->>WS: auth.ValidateToken(token)
    alt Invalid Token
        WS-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized (no upgrade)
    else Valid Token
        WS-->>Client: 101 Switching Protocols
        WS->>WS: hub.Register(client)
    end
```

### Matchmaking Flow
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as User A (WebSocket)
    participant Hub as WS Hub
    participant R as Redis
    participant W as Matchmaker Worker
    participant B as User B (WebSocket)

    A->>Hub: {type: "match.find", preferences: {...}}
    Hub->>R: ZADD waiting_pool + HSET ticket:A

    Note over W: Worker tick (every 500ms)
    W->>R: ZRANGEBYSCORE waiting_pool
    W->>R: HGETALL ticket:A, ticket:B
    W->>W: Separate normal/shadow pools
    W->>W: isCompatible(A, B, waitTime)?
    W->>R: ZREM + DEL tickets

    W->>Hub: NotifyMatch(A, B, roomID)
    Hub-->>A: {type: "match.found", peer: B, room: "..."}
    Hub-->>B: {type: "match.found", peer: A, room: "..."}
```

### Stripe VIP Payment
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant API as Go API
    participant Stripe
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Client->>API: POST /api/checkout (authenticated)
    API->>Stripe: Create Checkout Session
    Stripe-->>API: session.url
    API-->>Client: {url: "https://checkout.stripe.com/..."}
    Client->>Stripe: Complete payment

    Stripe->>API: POST /api/webhook/stripe
    API->>API: webhook.ConstructEvent(payload, sig, secret)
    alt Invalid Signature
        API-->>Stripe: 400 Bad Request
    else Valid
        API->>DB: UPDATE users SET is_vip = TRUE WHERE id = ?
        API-->>Stripe: 200 OK
    end
```

